findRootWithBisection(Function, double, double, int) - Static method in class app.rootFinding.RootFinding
A static method that use the Bisection algorithm to find 1 root in a range [a,b]
Conditions of work :
- the function have to be monotone and continuous in the range [a,b]
findRootWithNewtonRaphson(Function, Function, double, double, int) - Static method in class app.rootFinding.RootFinding
A static method that use the Newton Raphson algorithm to find 1 root in a range [a,b]
Conditions of work :
- the function have to be continuous in the range [a,b]
- the function can be derived
findRootWithSecant(Function, double, double, int) - Static method in class app.rootFinding.RootFinding
A static method that use the Scant algorithm to find 1 root
Conditions of work :
- We have to give it 2 point like approximation of the root

functionParse(String) - Method in class app.function.Function
Transform a string to a binary tree
Exemple : - x+2 : it gives root = "+" , left son = "x" ,right son ="2"
- sin(x) : it gives root = "sin" , left son = null , right son = "x"

Rule's : - braket are not obligatory but use it's to express priority
